<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="250" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The British Minister of Supply</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Beaverbrook</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Presidents Special Assistant</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,
                                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-01">January 1,
                                        1942</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Harry</hi>, Cables &amp; Wireless will
                                agree to the proposals for prohibiting transmissions by wireless
                                from South America to Italy and Tokyo.</p>
                            <p>Cables &amp; Wireless warn me that diplomatic action in South America
                                will be necessary, as the services there are controlled by local
                                companies.</p>
                            <p>I am getting a cable on the subject tomorrow and I will then write
                                another letter.</p>
                            <p>Yours ever,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Max</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>